rComments: One of my favourite prof so far, lectures go by so quickly with him.
I like him, he has lots of discussion time in class which is great
The Professor had well structured classes and the tests and exam were easy, people that didn't do well in the course simply didn't study. He used interesting videos and the class was informative.

He was a nice prof but didn't seem to have a thorough enough understanding of the material to teach it in a clear and concise manner. He wasn't confident with his answers, so many times I had to look things up on my own time to make sure I was not being taught something incorrect.

Nice Professor, funny, has interesting introductions for each new topic. Listens to students' opinions (almost too much). He is new and sometimes does not know the answer, but tries to make sense out of the question as best he can. Overall good course, interesting ideas in the lectures, the textbook is not good though, too unscientific.

New prof that can ten to get overswept with student questions that take up time in explaining his concepts. Overall not a difficult course, non culimative exam, half multiple choice and half essay questions which are short and can be found in the textbook. Textbook isn't that great of a read, long chapters that provides more examples than substance

He is a new prof and has a hard time with organization during lectures. He forgets definitions and many times students point out that something on the slide seems wrong. He looks and then agrees that what he said is probably wrong. It makes it very difficult to study his slides for exams, so I try to get as much info from the textbook as possible.
